A serving police officer has been charged with false imprisonment and rape. Christopher Henderson, 40, worked in Greater Manchester Police’s (GMP) City of Manchester district. He was arrested on suspicion of rape on Tuesday and taken into custody for further questioning. Henderson has now been charged with false imprisonment and rape and continues to be suspended while investigations are carried out. He will attend Manchester and Salford Magistrates court today. Got a story? Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. Or you can submit your videos and pictures here. For more stories like this, check our news page. Follow Metro.co.uk on Twitter and Facebook for the latest news updates. You can now also get Metro.co.uk articles sent straight to your device. Sign up for our daily push alerts here.